"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-olympics-2024-sky-brown-skateboarding-surfing-b1175155.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  Sport|Olympics  Sky Brownbattled to a brave bronze in Tuesday's skateboarding park final, then immediately set her sights on becoming a two-sport Olympian in Los Angeles in four years' time.  Brown overcame a heavy qualifying fall on the shoulder she had dislocated less than a fortnight ago tomake the podium for the second time, becoming the youngestTeam GBathlete to win medals at multipleOlympic Games.  The 16-year-old, who will now undergo surgery on her shoulder, also attempted to qualify for thesurfingat the2024 Olympics, competing at the World Surfing Games in Puerto Rico in March.  Doing so may have been a logistical impossibility in any case, given the women's medals were only awarded in the early hours of Tuesday morning, almost 10,000 miles away from Paris, in Tahiti.  That, though, is unlikely to be an issue in LA and Brown, who spends much of her time in California, is desperate to be in action on two boards.  Olympics 2024 medal table and latest count today  Olympics 2024: Every Team GB medal winner at the Paris Games so far  \\\"I am a double Olympic medallist,\\\" she said. \\\"It's really cool and I am very happy. When I go to LA, I am hoping to be a double Olympian there in surfing and skating. Every time I lose, I learn, and I learn a lot every day and I can bring that to LA.\\\"  There are, however, other tasks for the teenager to tick off before then.  \\\"I have some school work to do,\\\" she added. \\\"I can get my driver's licence in America. I miss surfing right now, so I am hoping to get into the water straight away. And I need to get a shoulder surgery, but hopefully that will not take too long.\\\"  Brown's participation in the final had at one stage looked in doubt, with the youngster in obvious discomfort when leaving the course at the end of qualifying. Afterwards, her father, Stewart, revealed she had effectively dislocated her shoulder again.  \\\"It came out and popped back in,\\\" he said. \\\"She did not even tell [the medical staff] it came out, because she was afraid they would pull her out. I ran down to her and she said, 'Daddy, it's come out'. Then, as we were getting up, she said, 'Oh, I think it's gone back in'.\\\"  Remarkably, Brown was the oldest member of a podium that was headed by 14-year-old Australian Arisa Trew, with 15-year-old Japanese Cocona Hiraki taking silver.  The contrast on Wednesday afternoon, then, will be stark, when 51-year-old Andy MacDonald, a multiple X Games gold medalist, makes his Olympic debut.  \\\"Honestly, I do not understand half of the tricks he does,\\\" Brown said of her team-mate. \\\"I definitely need some tips from him.\\\"  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\"}"